cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses bibliometric measurement in the life sciences, which involves analyzing research output and author contributions. This could fall under several arXiv CS sub-categories, but the most likely are cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.CY (Computers and Society), as they both deal with information management and analysis. Other possible categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as they also involve analyzing and measuring data.
